Description: A hemispherical jar-seal: of brown clay with an impressed inscription around the side and two more crossing at right angles over the top.The surface of the clay is in good condition, although rather worn.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XXIX, 83; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pls.58, abb.209; see also vols. I, 145 and II, 825, n.829; 1120, 1130.
